# Development Workflow

## Getting Started
1. Install dependencies: `pnpm install`
2. Start development server: `pnpm dev`
3. Build for production: `pnpm build` then `pnpm dist`

## Key Scripts
- `pnpm dev` - Starts both Next.js and Electron in development mode
- `pnpm dev:next` - Starts only the Next.js development server
- `pnpm dev:electron` - Starts only the Electron app
- `pnpm build` - Builds the Next.js app and Electron code
- `pnpm dist` - Creates distributable packages

## Important Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project configuration and scripts
- [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs) - Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - TailwindCSS configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

Always use `pnpm` as the package manager for this project.
